The FA for the Pacific Coast (FA6) Area issued by the Aviation Weather Center (AWC) at 
Kansas City, Missouri, and valid during the period beginning 1945, in part, follows:
Southern California costal areas will have broken clouds 1,000 to 2,000 feet msl with tops at 
4,000 feet.  The outlook is marginal VFR (MVFR, ceilings between 1,000 and 3,000 feet, and 
visibility between 3 to 5 miles) with broken ceilings.  Southern California inland areas will be 
